Goal
Rapidly separate informational/noise from true risk, assign ownership, and drive consistent next steps. 
Inputs
•	DLP alert record (policy match, detected data type, action, context, user, destination) 
•	Related activity history (patterns over time) 
Steps
1.	Confirm the Alert Type
	Single event vs aggregate/threshold alert  
	If aggregate: note threshold basis (count, volume, time window) 
2.	Initial Classification
	Potential False Positive: expected workflow; low-risk destination; data mis-detected 
	Potential True Positive: risky destination/action; repeated pattern; unusual context 
3.	Set Priority (Recommended Template)
	Base on: 
	content risk (sensitivity) 
	exfiltration risk (destination/action) 
	policy risk (how the policy is intended to behave) 
4.	Assign Ownership + Document
	Assign triage owner and add tags/comments for tracking  
	If your org uses a case/ticketing system, ensure a trackable record is created  
Output
•	“Close as informational” or “Escalate to investigation” with owner + priority + notes. 
